 between military lawyers and administration appointees, and political interference in criminal prosecutions that would be shocking within the traditional civilian and military justice systems. With the Obama administration planning to try the alleged 9/11 conspirators at Guantanamo-and vindicate the legal experiment the Bush administration could barely get off the ground-The Terror Courts could not be more timely.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMilitary courtsxCubaxGuantánamo Bay Naval BasexCubaxGuantánamo Bay Naval BasexUnited States. 0aMilitary courtszCubazGuantánamo Bay Naval Base. 0aMilitary courtszCubazGuantánamo Bay Naval Base. 0aWar crime trialsxUnited States. 0aWar crime trialszUnited States. 7aHISTORY / United States / 21st Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030019134940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300191349423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300191349/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles